Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dialog systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to belief tracking using neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed model uses attention mechanisms and non-parametric prediction. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the lack of flexibility in previous approaches and proposes a more universal and scalable solution. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper uses neural networks for the proposed model.
